description: Three photojournalists have created an in-depth report on electronic waste — its negative and ... positive ... consequences.
title: Stunning photos of a vast e-waste dumping ground — and those who make a living off it

description: The renowned North Carolina landmark and tourist attraction was slammed by the remnants of Hurricane Helene. The estate says parts of the entrance and farm were damaged and some animals were lost.
title: The historic Biltmore Estate, an Asheville icon, works to recover from Helene damage

description: As Election Day approaches, many Americans are questioning the secrecy of their ballots. We explain what you should know about privacy and casting a ballot.
title: Can someone find out who you voted for? No. Here is what you should know

description: NPR's Scott Simon wishes we could text them back when politicians message us asking for campaign donations.
title: Opinion: Political texts are pinging off the rails

description: For the past several weeks, the beloved beaver has been embroiled in a court battle over whether she should return to the wild or stay at the rescue center where she has lived since she was a newborn.
title: Why Massachusetts loves Nibi the beaver and is fighting to keep her out of the wild

description: Policymakers in California embrace a proven but unorthodox treatment for meth and cocaine addiction: Give people gift cards to stay off the drugs.
title: A controversial but effective treatment for meth addiction gains ground

description: For six decades, coal has provided for — and polluted — the Navajo Nation. Demolition of a power plant brings mixed emotions.
title: A coal power plant demolition serves as a poignant historical moment for the Navajo

description: New legislatures could overhaul school vouchers in Arizona, give the Democratic governor more clout in Kansas, and counter a progressive trend in Minnesota.
title: Three states show how abortion, schools and taxes are at stake in legislature races

description: The rally will mark Trump's first time back in the Pennsylvania city since the failed assassination attempt against him in July. The guest list will include a shooting survivor, as well as Elon Musk.
title: Trump is returning to Butler, the site of the 1st assassination attempt against him

description:
The October 7th Hamas-led attacks on Israel and the subsequent Israeli invasion of Gaza has changed the course of geopolitics and will have far reaching consequences for the world. The events have also upended the lives of countless individuals. Our team of reporters in the region bring us stories of lives changed in Israel, Gaza and the West Bank.

Sign up for State of the World+ to listen sponsor-free and support the work of NPR journalists around the world. Visit plus.npr.org.
title: October 7th: A Year of War Through the Eyes of Those Who Lived It
